  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Marketing Manager",
  "description": "<p>Nanyang Institute of Social Sciences (NISS) is an institute of higher education registered with SkillsFuture Singapore (SSG) under the Ministry of Education of Singapore, aiming to create a lifelong learning platform that incorporates quality higher education resources from the East and the West. <br /></p><p>We are now inviting applications for the position <strong>Marketing Manager</strong>, responsible for the overall marketing strategy and execution of the School’s academic programmes, leading the marketing team to build and scale the function, and overseeing overall marketing performance.</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Develop and execute marketing strategies across all social media and online channels.</li><li>Manage social media and online platforms, optimize advertising campaigns, and improve ROI.</li><li>Oversee content direction and design style, driving continuous updates and iterations.</li><li>Explore offline channels to achieve omnichannel coverage.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree or above; majors in Marketing, Advertising, Communications, Business, or related fields preferred.</li><li>Experience in marketing team management, project management, or the higher education sector is a plus.</li><li>Strong understanding of social media platforms and digital channels, including\nadvertising operations.</li><li>Skilled in a variety of marketing tools and techniques, including graphic design and video editing.</li><li>Excellent writing and content creation skills, with a keen eye for detail and quality.</li></ul>",
